; Top 5 refers to the candidates with the highest total support amounts from interest groups; 
; Interest group support can influence candidate voting behaviors;
; "Healthcare Reform" is a key piece of legislation that candidates often have strong opinions on.

; 
Financial support refers to the total amount received from interest groups that supported a candidate, while financial opposition refers to the total amount received from interest groups that opposed the candidate; 
A positive difference in support and opposition means that the candidate has received more financial support than opposition.
